# SecureScope environment template (Next.js / Vercel)
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local development. On Vercel, set variables in Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# === Client-safe (NEXT_PUBLIC_*) — non-secret flags only ===
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://your-deployment.vercel.app
#
# === Server-only API keys (never NEXT_PUBLIC_) ===
# These must be read from `process.env` inside `app/api/**` or server components only.
# VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, Twilio, etc. already follow this pattern in this repo.
#
# === Planned provider integrations (server routes — add when wiring) ===
# MXTOOLBOX_API_KEY=
# HETRIXTOOLS_API_KEY=
# ABUSEIPDB_API_KEY=
# VIRUSTOTAL_API_KEY=
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
# MS_GRAPH_CLIENT_SECRET=
# MS_GRAPH_CLIENT_ID=
# MS_GRAPH_TENANT_ID=
#
# If you are migrating from a Vite-style template, rename `VITE_*` secrets to the
# variables above and **do not** prefix secret API keys with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`, or they
# will be exposed in the browser bundle.
